Scala version conflicts**\\n\\nI’m considering what happens if the driver adds actor version 2.0.0-M1 while the build has 1.1.5. I wonder if Gradle will pick the latest version, which likely means 2.0.0-M1 since it's a milestone release. For scala-reflect, it should choose version 2.13.18 over 2.13.17. Scala compatibility is essential, meaning the compiler needs to match the library version. I’m debating whether to add both scala-compiler and scala-library at 2.13.18 to avoid conflicts, as existing dependencies may not align.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Pekko Parsing 2.0.0-M1 is a small internal Scala macro artifact; its usable classes reference provided Pekko Actor and Scala reflection APIs, so meaningful tests need those provided dependencies available on the test classpath.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The artifact POM declares pekko-actor_2.13 as a provided dependency, and LogHelper references org.apache.pekko.event.LoggingAdapter and Pekko annotations.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.scala-lang:scala-reflect:2.13.18\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The artifact POM declares scala-reflect 2.13.18 as a provided dependency, and LogHelperMacro uses scala.reflect.macros.blackbox.Context.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.scala-lang:scala-compiler:2.13.18\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Meaningful coverage of the macro API requires compiling Scala test code that invokes the def macros.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, environment variable, or system property appears necessary. Do not base the fix on org.apache.pekko.http.ccompat.pre213/since213; those classes are absent from pekko-parsing_2.13:2.0.0-M1. Focus on org.apache.pekko.macros.LogHelper and LogHelperMacro. If Scala source extends or directly uses LogHelper, place the test helper in an org.apache.pekko.* package because the trait is private[pekko]; otherwise use reflection for class-loading coverage.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The 2.0.0-M1 jar only contains internal macro support classes, so public API surface is very small.\",\n    \"Tests that exercise Scala macro expansion can be brittle across Scala/Pekko versions; keep coverage focused on current 2.0.0-M1 classes rather than removed cross-version compatibility annotations.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e6a8ad0ca813cc9016a42f9bff4d48195a68db53e6cdf4aef\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 314, "output": 2371, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24189, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782774181761, "responseId": "resp_0e6a8ad0ca813cc9016a42f9a667a08195852f45333e626143"}}
